questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot microservice deployed on a Tomcat container experiences progressive Heap memory exhaustion and frequent Full GCs. You isolate the issue to a newly introduced performance monitoring aspect:

java
@Aspect
@Component
public class PerformanceMonitorAspect {
    private static final ThreadLocal<MonitorContext> contextHolder = ThreadLocal.withInitial(MonitorContext::new);

    @Around("@annotation(Monitored)")
    public Object monitor(ProceedingJoinPoint pjp) throws Throwable {
        MonitorContext ctx = contextHolder.get();
        ctx.startTimer(pjp.getSignature().toShortString());
        try {
            return pjp.proceed();
        } finally {
            ctx.stopTimer();
        }
    }
}
